{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:proverbs.25",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 25,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 25 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.25.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:1",
      "text": "These are also proverbs of Solomon, which the men of Hezekiah king of Judah copied out.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.25.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:2",
      "text": "It is the glory of God to conceal a thing: but the honour of kings is to search out a matter.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.25.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:3",
      "text": "The heaven for height, and the earth for depth, and the heart of kings is unsearchable.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.25.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:4",
      "text": "Take away the dross from the silver, and there shall come forth a vessel for the finer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.25.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:5",
      "text": "Take away the wicked from before the king, and his throne shall be established in righteousness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.25.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:6",
      "text": "Put not forth thyself in the presence of the king, and stand not in the place of great men:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.25.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:7",
      "text": "For better it is that it be said unto thee, Come up hither; than that thou shouldest be put lower in the presence of the prince whom thine eyes have seen.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.25.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:8",
      "text": "Go not forth hastily to strive, lest thou know not what to do in the end thereof, when thy neighbour hath put thee to shame.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.25.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:9",
      "text": "Debate thy cause with thy neighbour himself; and discover not a secret to another:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.25.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:10",
      "text": "Lest he that heareth it put thee to shame, and thine infamy turn not away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.25.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:11",
      "text": "A word fitly spoken is like apples of gold in pictures of silver.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.25.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:12",
      "text": "As an earring of gold, and an ornament of fine gold, so is a wise reprover upon an obedient ear.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.25.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:13",
      "text": "As the cold of snow in the time of harvest, so is a faithful messenger to them that send him: for he refresheth the soul of his masters.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.25.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:14",
      "text": "Whoso boasteth himself of a false gift is like clouds and wind without rain.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.25.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:15",
      "text": "By long forbearing is a prince persuaded, and a soft tongue breaketh the bone.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.25.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:16",
      "text": "Hast thou found honey? eat so much as is sufficient for thee, lest thou be filled therewith, and vomit it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.25.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:17",
      "text": "Withdraw thy foot from thy neighbour’s house; lest he be weary of thee, and so hate thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.25.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:18",
      "text": "A man that beareth false witness against his neighbour is a maul, and a sword, and a sharp arrow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.25.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:19",
      "text": "Confidence in an unfaithful man in time of trouble is like a broken tooth, and a foot out of joint.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.25.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:20",
      "text": "As he that taketh away a garment in cold weather, and as vinegar upon nitre, so is he that singeth songs to an heavy heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.25.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:21",
      "text": "If thine enemy be hungry, give him bread to eat; and if he be thirsty, give him water to drink:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.25.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:22",
      "text": "For thou shalt heap coals of fire upon his head, and the Lord shall reward thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.25.23",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:23",
      "text": "The north wind driveth away rain: so doth an angry countenance a backbiting tongue.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.25.24",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:24",
      "text": "It is better to dwell in the corner of the housetop, than with a brawling woman and in a wide house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.25.25",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:25",
      "text": "As cold waters to a thirsty soul, so is good news from a far country.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.25.26",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:26",
      "text": "A righteous man falling down before the wicked is as a troubled fountain, and a corrupt spring.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.25.27",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:27",
      "text": "It is not good to eat much honey: so for men to search their own glory is not glory.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:proverbs.25.28",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 25,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 25:28",
      "text": "He that hath no rule over his own spirit is like a city that is broken down, and without walls.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
